# Email Service Configuration Example
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your SMTP credentials

# =============================================================================
# SMTP Configuration (Required for sending emails)
# =============================================================================

# SMTP Server Settings
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_SECURE=false

# SMTP Authentication
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password-here

# Sender Information
SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@emtelaak.com
SMTP_FROM_NAME=Emtelaak Platform

# Frontend URL (for email links)
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

# =============================================================================
# Provider-Specific Examples
# =============================================================================

# --- Gmail (Development/Testing) ---
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx  # App password from Google Account
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=your-email@gmail.com

# --- SendGrid (Recommended for Production) ---
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=apikey  # Literally the word "apikey"
# SMTP_PASSWORD=SG.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx  # Your SendGrid API key
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@emtelaak.com

# --- AWS SES ---
# SMTP_HOST=email-smtp.us-east-1.amazonaws.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=AKIAXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX  # Your AWS SMTP username
# SMTP_PASSWORD=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx  # Your AWS SMTP password
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@emtelaak.com

# --- Mailgun ---
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.mailgun.org
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=postmaster@your-domain.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@your-domain.com

# --- Mailtrap (Testing Only) ---
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.mailtrap.io
# SMTP_PORT=2525
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# SMTP_PASSWORD=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@emtelaak.com

# =============================================================================
# Notes
# =============================================================================
# 
# 1. If SMTP credentials are not configured, emails will be logged to console
#    instead of being sent (useful for development)
# 
# 2. For Gmail, you must use an App Password, not your account password:
#    - Enable 2-Factor Authentication
#    - Go to Security â†’ App passwords
#    - Generate a new app password for "Mail"
# 
# 3. For production, use a dedicated email service like SendGrid or AWS SES
#    for better deliverability and analytics
# 
# 4. SMTP_FROM_EMAIL should match your verified sender domain
# 
# 5. FRONTEND_URL is used to generate links in emails (login, password reset)
# 
# 6. See EMAIL_SERVICE_SETUP.md for detailed configuration instructions
# 
# =============================================================================
